 :feature creature: /n./ [poss. fr. slang `creature feature' for a horror
movie] 1. One who loves to add features to designs or programs, perhaps at
the expense of coherence, concision, or {taste}. 2. Alternately, a mythical
being that induces otherwise rational programmers to perpetrate such crocks.
see also {feeping creaturism}, {creeping featurism}.